Melania and Donald Trump extend their greetings to Jewish people celebrating Hanukkah in the United States, Israel, and around the world. They acknowledge the historical significance of the lighting of the menorah and the persecution that Jews have faced throughout history. The Trumps also express their condolences to the victims of the Tree of Life synagogue shooting in Pittsburgh and pledge their support to the affected families and community. They hope that the holiday season brings peace and happiness, emphasizing the power of light to overcome darkness.